==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gneiss
<hw>Gneiss</hw> <pr>(n⟦imac⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.]</ety>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A crystalline rock, consisting, like granite, of
quartz, feldspar, and mica, but having these materials, especially the
mica, arranged in planes, so that it breaks rather easily into coarse
slabs or flags. Hornblende sometimes takes the place of the mica, and it
is then called <stype>hornblendic gneiss</stype> <it>or</it>
<stype>syenitic gneiss</stype>. Similar varieties of related rocks are
also called gneiss.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gneissic</ent>⟦br⟧
